Exempt MSVC from awk.h's `__STDC__` hard-error.

Upstream `awk.h:55-58` `#error`s out if `__STDC__` isn't defined as `>= 1`,
mirroring an existing exemption for SunPro. MSVC's `cl.exe` only defines
`__STDC__` under the `/Za` strict-ANSI option (which disables MS
extensions we need), so out of the box gawk refuses to compile under
MSVC. Adding `&& !defined(_MSC_VER)` to the outer guard mirrors the
SunPro carve-out and lets the build proceed.

Without this patch we would have to predefine `__STDC__=1` for MSVC,
which in turn makes MSVC's `<sys/stat.h>` hide its POSIX `struct stat`
alias — forcing further `#define stat _stat` shimming. This one-line
patch eliminates that whole chain.

--- awk.h
+++ awk.h
@@ -52,7 +52,7 @@
 #endif /* LOCALEDIR */
 #endif

-#if !defined(__SUNPRO_C)
+#if !defined(__SUNPRO_C) && !defined(_MSC_VER)
 #if !defined(__STDC__) || __STDC__ < 1
 #error "gawk no longer supports non-C89 environments (no __STDC__ or __STDC__ < 1)"
 #endif
